# Ancient-Shape Physics — White Paper Series

**Author:** Michael Scott Shaffer (Siren Sinfull)
**Framework Development:** 2004–2026 (22 years)
**Papers Formalized:** June 2025 – February 2026

---

## Overview

Ancient-Shape Physics is an integer-only, topology-first framework for modeling recursive systems across all scales of reality. It replaces floating-point approximation with exact integer arithmetic, replaces division with boundary folding, and replaces infinite divergences with finite Mobium loops.

The framework is built on three additive kernels — mitosis (2x−1), stable (2x), and growth (2x+1) — which constitute the minimum and sufficient operations for all generative recursion.

---

