---

## The Core Claim

Three operations — **x+x−1**, **x+x**, **x+x+1** — applied recursively from any seed, produce contiguous coverage of the entire number line. The tier sizes follow Mersenne numbers (2ⁿ−1). No gaps. Any seed. Any scale.

This is not an approximation. It is arithmetic. It is verifiable in three lines of code.

---

## Reading Order

The papers are numbered sequentially and each builds on its predecessors. Start with Paper I. By Paper X, the entire framework is established.

For those coming from conventional physics: Papers I, II, and III establish the operational vocabulary. Paper VI is where the dimensional framework diverges from standard spacetime. Paper VII is the cosmological model. Paper X is the synthesis.

For those coming from computer science: Papers I–III give you the algorithm. Paper IV gives you scalable measurement. Paper VIII gives you game architecture. The [implementation repositories](#related-repositories) contain running code.

